      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:1:2:9:2",
      "text": [
        " أَبُو عَبْدِ اللَّهِ ( عليه السلام ) لِحُمْرَانَ بْنِ أَعْيَنَ فِي شَيْ‏ءٍ سَأَلَهُ إِنَّمَا يَهْلِكُ النَّاسُ لِأَنَّهُمْ لَا يَسْأَلُونَ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin yahya, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad Bin Isa, from Hammad Bin Isa, from Hareyz, from Zurara and Muhammad Bin Muslim and Bureyd Al Ijaly who said, ",
          "‘Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> said to Humran Bin Ayn regarding something he had asked him<sup>asws</sup>: ‘But rather, the people are destroyed because they are not asking’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          " 2. Muhammad ibn Yahya has narrated from Ahmad ibn Muhammad ibn ‘Isa from Hammed ibn ‘Isa from Hariz from Zurra, Muhammad ibn Muslim and Burayd al-‘Ijli who has said the following. “(Imam) abu ‘Abdallah (a.s.) has said, ‘People are destroyed only because they do not ask (what they do not know).’”"
        ]
      }
    }
